wikipedia_page.main: Baroness Bethsabée de Rothschild (assumed the name  Batsheva after she immigrated to Israel in 1951; 23 September 1914 – 20 April 1999) was a philanthropist, a patron of dance, and member of the Rothschild banking family.

response: * Bethsabée de Rothschild (1914–1999),  Jewish philanthropist, daughter of Édouard Alphonse de Rothschild

One of Graham's students was heiress Bethsabée de Rothschild with whom she became close friends. When Rothschild moved to Israel and established the Batsheva Dance Company in 1965, Graham became the company's first director.
